
[1]acorus

   A'CORUS, n. [L. from Gr..]

   1. Aromatic Calamus, sweet flag, or sweet rush.

   2. In natural history, blue coral, which grows in the form of a tree,
   on a rocky bottom, in some parts of the African seas. it is brought
   from the Camarones and Benin.

   3. In medicine, this name is sometimes given to the great galangal.
